{%- comment -%}
  Journal Article — From Studio to Your Door
{%- endcomment -%}

<article class="isyf-article-page">
  <div class="isyf-article-hero-wrapper">
    {%- if section.settings.image != blank -%}
      <img class="isyf-article-hero-image" src="{{ section.settings.image | image_url: width: 2000 }}" alt="From studio to your door">
    {%- else -%}
      <img class="isyf-article-hero-image" src="{{ 'journal-3.jpg' | asset_url }}" alt="From studio to your door">
    {%- endif -%}
    <div class="isyf-article-hero-overlay"></div>
    <div class="isyf-article-hero-content">
      <span class="isyf-article-hero-label">BEHIND THE SCENES</span>
      <h1 class="isyf-article-hero-title">From Studio to Your Door</h1>
      <span class="isyf-article-hero-date">March 2026</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="isyf-article-body">
    <p class="isyf-article-intro">
      You've placed your order. The confirmation email hits your inbox. But what happens between that click and the moment you unwrap your new favourite piece? Here's a look behind the curtain at the journey every ISYF garment takes from our studio to your door.
    </p>

    <h2>The order comes in</h2>

    <p>
      When you place an order on iseeyoufeel.com, our system processes it within minutes. For ISYF Premium pieces — our pre-produced collection of knits, blazers, and tailored essentials — the item is pulled from our carefully managed inventory in our fulfilment centre.
    </p>
    <p>
      For ISYF FEELS pieces — hoodies, graphic tees, embroidered items — the process is different. Because we operate on a print-on-demand model, your order triggers production. This isn't a compromise; it's a choice. Every ISYF FEELS garment is made to order, which means zero waste, zero overproduction, and a piece that was literally made for you.
    </p>

    <h2>Made to order: the ISYF FEELS process</h2>

    <p>
      Once your ISYF FEELS order is placed, the production begins within 24 hours. Here's what happens:
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Day 1-2: Preparation.</strong> The base garment — a premium blank in the colour and size you selected — is prepared. We use 380gsm organic cotton for hoodies and 220gsm ringspun cotton for t-shirts, sourced from certified mills.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Day 2-3: Print or embroidery.</strong> For printed pieces, we use DTG (direct-to-garment) printing with water-based inks that are OEKO-TEX certified. The result is a print that's soft to the touch, vibrant in colour, and resistant to fading. For embroidered pieces, our partner atelier stitches each design using industrial embroidery machines that replicate the precision of hand-stitching, with thread density that ensures the design stays crisp through years of wear.
    </p>
    <p>
      <strong>Day 3-4: Quality control.</strong> Every single piece is inspected before packaging. We check print alignment, colour accuracy, stitching quality, and overall finish. If anything doesn't meet our standard, the piece is rejected and remade. We'd rather delay your order by a day than send you something that isn't right.
    </p>

    <h2>Packaging with intention</h2>

    <p>
      We thought carefully about how our products arrive. The unboxing experience is part of the brand — it's the first physical touchpoint between ISYF and you.
    </p>
    <p>
      Each garment is folded with care and wrapped in acid-free tissue paper. It's placed in a matte black box (for Premium pieces) or a recycled mailer bag (for FEELS pieces). Inside, you'll find a small card with the garment's name and a line about the emotion that inspired it. No plastic, no excess filler, no materials that you'd immediately throw away.
    </p>
    <p>
      Our packaging materials are either recycled, recyclable, or compostable. The tissue paper is FSC-certified. The mailer bags are made from 80% recycled content. Even the tape is paper-based. These choices cost more than conventional packaging, but they align with who we are.
    </p>

    <h2>Shipping: what to expect</h2>

    <p>
      We ship worldwide from our fulfilment partners in Europe. Here's what the timeline looks like:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Europe:</strong> 5-10 business days. Free shipping on orders over 100 EUR.</li>
      <li><strong>North America:</strong> 7-14 business days. Free shipping on orders over 150 EUR.</li>
      <li><strong>Rest of world:</strong> 10-20 business days. Shipping calculated at checkout.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      For ISYF FEELS (print-on-demand) items, add 2-5 business days for production before shipping begins. We know this requires a little patience, but we believe the wait is worth it — you're receiving a piece that was made specifically for you, with no waste generated in the process.
    </p>
    <p>
      Every order includes tracking. You'll receive an email with your tracking number as soon as your package ships, and you can follow its journey in real-time.
    </p>

    <h2>The moment it arrives</h2>

    <p>
      We've heard from customers who tell us they take a moment before opening their ISYF package. Like savouring the anticipation before the first page of a new book. We love that.
    </p>
    <p>
      When you open the box, you should feel something — not just the fabric between your fingers, but the care that went into every step. The pattern that was revised fifteen times. The cotton that was sourced from a specific mill. The embroidery that was checked stitch by stitch. The tissue paper that was folded by hand.
    </p>

    <blockquote>
      "We don't just ship products. We deliver the bridge between what we see and what you feel."
      <cite>— The ISYF Team</cite>
    </blockquote>

    <h2>After the purchase</h2>

    <p>
      Our relationship doesn't end when the package arrives. If anything isn't right — the fit, the colour, the quality — we want to know. Our customer care team responds within 24 hours at contact@iseeyoufeel.com. We offer a 30-day return policy on unworn items with tags, with refunds processed within 5-7 business days.
    </p>
    <p>
      We also include care instructions with every garment, because we want your ISYF piece to last. Wash cold, air dry when possible, store knitwear folded. These small habits make a real difference in how long your garment keeps its shape, colour, and softness.
    </p>
    <p>
      From the first sketch to the moment you wear it out the door — every step is intentional. That's the ISYF way.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="isyf-article-footer">
    <a href="/pages/journal-design" class="isyf-article-next">
      <span class="isyf-article-next-label">NEXT ARTICLE</span>
      <span class="isyf-article-next-title">The Creative Process Behind ISYF</span>
    </a>
  </div>
</article>

